            <!-- Title -->
            <h1 class="text-primary text-center mb-4">Eligibility Criteria for MCA Admission</h1>

            <!-- Content -->
            <p>
                The duration of the MCA program has been revised from <strong>3 years to 2 years</strong>, in line with the updated guidelines outlined in the <strong>AICTE APH 2020-21</strong>. Candidates seeking admission must meet the following eligibility criteria:
            </p>

            <!-- Eligibility Qualifications -->
            <h4 class="mt-4 mb-3">Qualification Requirements</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>BCA (Bachelor of Computer Applications) or a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science Engineering, or an equivalent degree.</li>
                <li>B.Sc., B.Com., or B.A. with Mathematics at the 10+2 level or at the graduation level. Candidates from these backgrounds may need to complete additional bridge courses, depending on the specific norms of the university.</li>
            </ul>

            <!-- Academic Requirements -->
            <h4 class="mt-4 mb-3">Academic Requirements</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>A minimum of <strong>50% marks</strong> in the qualifying examination (for General category candidates).</li>
                <li>For candidates belonging to reserved categories (SC/ST/OBC), a minimum of <strong>45% marks</strong> in the qualifying examination.</li>
            </ul>

            <!-- Additional Notes -->
            <h4 class="mt-4 mb-3">Additional Notes</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>The percentage criteria are calculated based on the aggregate marks obtained in the qualifying examination.</li>
                <li>For candidates with degrees from foreign universities, the eligibility will be subject to an equivalence certificate issued by the concerned university or authority.</li>
                <li>Candidates must meet any other specific requirements or prerequisites as set by the respective university, which may include a valid entrance exam score or prior work experience in the field of computer science or related areas.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
